al features of personhood in each one of these traditions? The volume presents the concept of "person" in its different aspects as anchored in Judaism, Christianity, and Islam. It unfolds commonalities and differences between the three monotheistic religions as well as the manifold discourses about the meaning of "person" within these three religions.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aDialog. 4aDiskurs. 4aInterreligiösität. 4aPerson.  aInterreligious discourses.  adialogue.  aperson.1 aAlam, Edward J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBotwinick, Aryeh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEl Masri, Ghassan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRiddell, Peter G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTamer, Georges, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2024 Part 1z978311133219208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023 Englishz978311131928508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023z9783111318820oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831107568380 cprintz978311075664740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311075671540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110756715423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110756715/original  a978-3-11-131928-5  EBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE CO